"{'model': 'mistral:latest', 'response': '\"{ \\\\\"title\\\\\": \\\\\"Reverse Sentence Words (Medium)\\\\\", \\\\\"description\\\\\": \\\\\"Write a function `reverse_sentence` that takes a sentence as input and returns the same sentence with each word reversed. The words in the sentence are separated by spaces, commas, periods, question marks or exclamation points.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Function Signature\\\\\\\\n```python\\\\\\\\ndef reverse_sentence(s: str) -> str:\\\\\\\\n```\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Input\\\\\\\\n- `s` (str): A string containing a sentence that may contain spaces, commas, periods, question marks or exclamation points.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#### Output\\\\\\\\n- Returns the given sentence with each word reversed.\\\\\\\\n\\\\\", \\\\\"code\\\\\": \\\\\"def reverse_sentence(s: str) -> str:\\\\\\\\n    # Split the sentence into words\\\\\\\\n    words = s.split()\\\\\\\\n    # Reverse each word and join them back together\\\\\\\\n    return \\' \\'.join(word[::-1] for word in words)\\\\\", \\\\\"tests\\\\\": [\\\\\"assert reverse_sentence(\\'Hey there, how are you doing?\\') == \\'yeh tyerah , sihtyd ooh-ytednu\\',\\\\\", \\\\\"assert reverse_sentence(\\'I love Python programming!\\') == \\'mi gnitegrom ytpilnoP si sihlorb ym!\\'\\\\\"] }\"'}"